  "biography_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">Asclepiades of Mendes was a grammarian from the Egyptian city of Mendes, active during the 1st century BCE. No further biographical details of his life are preserved.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">His sole attested work is the lost treatise On the Grammar of Democritus, which analyzed the language of the pre-Socratic philosopher Democritus. Asclepiades is a minor but clear example of a specific Hellenistic scholarly genre: specialized grammatical studies of individual classical authors. His work’s mention in later sources like the Suda places him within the tradition of Alexandrian scholarship focused on textual and linguistic analysis.</p>\n</div>",
